This paper is likely to belong to the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL) as it deals with distributional semantics and phrase representations. It may also belong to "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) as it proposes a new composition model. Additionally, it could be categorized under "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) as it deals with natural language processing. "Information Retrieval" (cs.IR) is another possible category as the paper discusses methods for improving the representation of phrases. Finally, "Computational Complexity" (cs.CC) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on complexity theory, but it may be relevant due to the discussion of reducing the number of parameters needed for composition models.
